{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A8whRn2VYkEruubh5Lhjs1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ConfigMap update hasn't propagated to the pod's volume yet. Kubernetes ConfigMap volume mounts are eventually consistent - the kubelet syncs them periodically (usually every 60 seconds by default). Since the reload was triggered before the file was updated, Prometheus still has the old config.\n\nI have two options:\n1. Wait for the kubelet to sync the ConfigMap to the volume (up to ~60 seconds) and then reload again\n2. Restart the Prometheus pod, which will pick up the new ConfigMap\n\nLet me wait for the kubelet to sync and then reload. Or I could just restart the pod to force it.\nI'll give it a moment and check if the file has been updated on the volume.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":349,"cache_read_input_tokens":36027,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":349},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ce06994-a8d0-4fc8-b035-fa752d1456e6","uuid":"0c24a312-8e09-4576-a3e8-3d47a856e6fa","request_id":"req_011CcLu1cFtd2yzbXiuQ1bvP"}
